{"type":"message","id":"2185f7c3","parentId":"aa92e09b","timestamp":"2026-05-09T09:46:44.596Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so psutil only takes 58ms, and the full script completes quickly. The issue is that the cron job itself is timing out at 60 seconds - so the cron system is killing the process before it can finish.\n\nLooking at the jobs list again, the \"Cron Governor 每5分鐘系統監控\" job has:\n- schedule: every 3600000ms (1 hour) \n- description says \"每60分鐘系統監控（系統活動感知排程）— 20分鐘→60分鐘（降低系統負載）\"\n- timeoutSeconds: 60\n\nWait, the description says it was \"每20分鐘→60分鐘（降低系統負載）\" - so it was changed from 20 min to 60 min. But the message says \"每5分鐘\" which was probably the original.\n\n\nThe real problem is that the job's timeout of 60 seconds is way too short for an isolated agent session running this script. Even though the script itself completes in under a second, the cron system is killing it at 60 seconds - I need to increase the timeout setting to give it more breathing room.\n\nLooking at the actual execution times in the logs, most runs are taking 60-63 seconds, which means they're constantly hitting and exceeding that 60-second timeout. The fix is straightforward: bump the timeout up to 90 or 120 seconds to accommodate the actual execution time. But I should also dig into why the full isolated session takes this long - is it the Python script itself, the agent startup overhead, or something else in the infrastructure? Let me look at the cron job's message and timeout settings. The job is running with a 60-second timeout, but the actual execution is taking around 60-63 seconds based on the lastDurationMs values. The isolated agent session overhead likely includes module loading time, which could explain why it's consistently timing out at that threshold.\n\nI should increase the timeout to something more realistic like 90 seconds to account for this overhead. The description mentions \"每60分鐘系統監控\", but I need to verify the actual schedule interval since the job name says \"每5分鐘\" - there might be a mismatch between what the job is supposed to do and how it's currently configured. So the schedule is actually every 3600 seconds (1 hour), not 5 minutes as the name suggests—I was getting confused by the description that mentioned changing from 20 minutes to 60 minutes. The jobs list shows everyMs: 3600000, which is 1 hour, so that's consistent with the description noting the interval was increased. But the name \"每5分鐘\" implies it should run every 5 minutes, which contradicts both the schedule and the description. I need to increase the timeout from 60 to 90 seconds to give the job enough time to complete.\n","thinkingSignature":"7f3c016028b847fd321773428ad724352bf59da9ff153ef180abad189d8c85a9"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n腳本本身執行很快（~1秒），但 cron job timeout 是關鍵瓶頸。看 jobs 狀態：\n\n- `lastDurationMs: 60563`（60秒）\n- `lastError: \"cron: job execution timed out\"`\n- timeoutSeconds: 60 → 几乎每次都觸發超時\n\n**修正方案：把 timeout 60秒 → 90秒**\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zwvuvevw1b31_1","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"update","jobId":"8ecf6a44-2c50-4d77-b645-e226ac1a976d","patch":{"name":"Cron Governor 每60分鐘系統監控"},"payload":"{\"timeoutSeconds\": 90}"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":128,"output":765,"cacheRead":41184,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42077,"cost":{"input":0.0000384,"output":0.000918,"cacheRead":0.00247104,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00342744}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778319964673,"responseId":"064e355e8d7db99343c96b6b8dc917d2"}}
